title: Grateful Dead Live at Winterland Arena on 1978-12-31
lineage: 2 x AKG D224E >> Sony TC-158SD  >> MAC Analog Sound Preservation: MAC >> Nakamichi CR7a => Korg MR-1000 >> DSF [1-bit 5.6448 MHz Stereo] >> Korg MR-1000 => Korg AudioGate >> WAV [24/96] Taped By: Rheinhart Holwein
description:
Set 1

Sugar Magnolia-> Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Friend Of The Devil, It's All Over Now, Stagger Lee, From The Heart Of Me-> Sunshine Daydream

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, Ramble On Rose, I Need A Miracle*-> Terrapin Station-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums**-> Not Fade Away***-> Around & Around***

Set 3

Dark Star-> The Other One-> Dark Star-> Wharf Rat-> Saint Stephen-> Good Lovin', E:Casey Jones-> E: Johnny B. Goode, E: We Bid You Good Night****

*W Matt Kelly, **W Lee Oscar, Greg Errico, Ken Kesey Etc, ***W John Cippolina, Second Encore Simulcast FM - KSAN, TV - KQED Blues Brothers and NRPS Opened

reviews.review_text: sooo good deserves a second comment could be my all-time-favorite: Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain
The Closing of Winterland This was wonderful concert and I am so glad that I could be a part of it.  I had no idea at that time that we were making history!

Gratitude Thanks from the bottom of my heart to the top of my soul to the license holders, all concerned financial interests in connection with the commercial release of the award-winning recording of this concert, and IA Grateful Dead Forum.

This show is of course a top five essential to any Deadhead's collection.  Sad but true, in the course of my divorce, my partner and former best friend (though note, we are back to be going friends now) ended up with out entire tapes collection.  You don't want to know how that came down...

So anyway, here and now, we all have this via the library:  a way better recording.  Silver linings, huh.

Thank you, thank you, thank you;  I love you all.
Thank you! Thank you! Thank you! Thank you to all who made this recording possible and thank you to all who keep it available here.  A noble effort and one that I value to the greatest depths...
